news.title: UltraTech Cement's subsidiary to acquire 70% shares in Duqm Cement Project for $2.25 million
news.para: UltraTech Cement had reported a dip of 37.87 crore in its net consolidated profit during the quarter ended December 31, 2022. Its profit after tax (PAT) stood Rs 1,062.58 crore in Q3 FY23 as against Rs 1,710.14 crore it registered in the corresponding quarter of the previous fiscal

news.title: Kamdhenu Ventures posts Rs 3.25 crore net loss in Q3 FY23
news.para: Kamdhenu Ventures' net consolidated income stood at Rs 69.69 crore in Q3 FY23, a quarter-on-quarter growth of 8.08 per cent from Rs 64.48 crore it registered in the previous quarter of the financial year 2022-23.

news.title: Ajmera Realty's net profit up 9.58% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Ajmera Realty's total consolidated income stood at Rs 80.57 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 14.87 per cent from Rs 70.14 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Maharashtra CM announces 300 km metro network in two years
news.para: "We are working towards completing work on nearly 300km of metro network here which would be made operational in the next two years. The work on line 3 will also start soon,” said Shinde.

news.title: Cochin development body to digitalize rent collection
news.para: Once it is implemented, GCDA will be able to easily manage the allocation and renting-out of its shops, and create a database of its rent management using the software.

news.title: West Bengal set to amend land reforms act
news.para: It is likely to introduce a bill in the state assembly in the budget session. This bill is to garner revenue for the state exchequer as so far the land for commercial use was available for a 99-year lease.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC property tax kitty still 45% short of year's target
news.para: The targeted property tax collection for the year as announced in the civic budget 2022-23 by the BMC chief was Rs 7,000 crore. This means around 55% of the targeted property tax has been collected for the year.

news.title: Noida: Flat sold twice, builder of Shivalik Homes booked for fraud after HC order
news.para: Officers at the Surajpur police station said they had already initiated an investigation and action would be initiated against the builder.

news.title: K Raheja Corp, Modern India ink pact to develop 1-million-sq-ft project in Mumbai
news.para: The project will be developed through an agreement for sale of the plot currently owned by Modern India that has business interest spanning across infrastructure, power generation and real estate.

news.title: Macrotech Developers aims to cut debt by nearly 40% in 2023: MD
news.para: Mumbai-based Macrotech Developers, which is one of the leading real estate firms in the country, markets its properties under the Lodha brand.

news.title: Gurugram: Tashee Capital Gateway buyers protest over delayed possession
news.para: According to the protesters, the project was launched in 2011. The builder-buyer agreements were signed in 2013 with the promise of delivery of flats by December 2015.

news.title: Rajasthan government used JDA, RHB to raze illegal buildings, acquire land
news.para: The civic body had demolished 18 big buildings in 2019, 20 in 2020, 16 in 2021 and 22 in 2022. The year started off with fresh waves of demolitions.

news.title: Lack of checks at construction sites kicks up dust, makes Mumbai ill
news.para: A large number of Mumbaikars are now complaining about dust from construction sites polluting the air they breathe. In fact, a 2020 study by NEERI and IIT-B clearly showed road or construction dust as the source of over 70% of the particulate matter (PM) load in Mumbai’s air.

news.title: Kolkata civic body struggles to pull down unsafe buildings
news.para: ​According to a source in the KMC buildings department, though the demolition work was handed over to a private agency a month-and-a-half ago, the agency has so far been able to raze only portions.

news.title: Six lakh residents yet to pay property tax in Chennai
news.para: An enforcement drive would be conducted soon to collect property tax, officials said, adding that so far they had received a tax revenue of 1,240 crore in the financial year 2022-23.
